  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure provisions\n- Mandatory reporting of large transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Prosecutorial actions\n- International cooperation\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training\n- Internal monitoring systems\n\n6. Predicate Offenses\n- Defining underlying criminal activities\n- Establishing legal connections to money laundering\n\n7. Technological Adaptations\n- Regulations addressing digital currencies\n- Cybercrime money laundering provisions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining economic transparency.",
